"Abstract Developments in the area of international cryptography continue apace. In this regular series of articles, I have usually chosen either to discuss an item of current topical interest or, alternatively, review the historical development of a particular policy issue in rather greater depth. This month, I propose to look at a number of miscellaneous items of recent news, each of which, by itself, would not justify a whole article, but each of which is nonetheless worthy of an honourable mention as part of the wider tapestry of international activity."
